AS OF DECEMBER 31, 2005,

THE COMPANY CONVERTED TO THE RP (RETIREMENT PLANS) 2000 MORTALITY TABLE FOR

CALCULATING THE YEAR-END 2005 U.S. PENSION AND POSTRETIREMENT OBLIGATIONS AND

2006 EXPENSE. THE IMPACT OF THIS CHANGE INCREASED THE YEAR-END 2005 U.S.

PROJECTED BENEFIT OBLIGATIONS FOR PENSION BY $385 MILLION, THE YEAR-END 2005

U.S. ACCUMULATED BENEFIT OBLIGATIONS FOR PENSION BY $349 MILLION AND THE 2005

U.S. ACCUMULATED POSTRETIREMENT BENEFIT OBLIGATION BY $93 MILLION. THIS CHANGE

ALSO INCREASED PENSION EXPENSES FOR 2006 BY $64 MILLION AND POSTRETIREMENT

EXPENSES BY $17 MILLION.

